The .223 Wylde hybrid chamber was designed by Bill Wylde of Greenup, IL to exploit the accuracy advantages of the .223 Remington commercial chambering without pressure problems or compromising the functional reliability when using the high velocity 5.56x45mm NATO military ammunition. It is used by many rifle manufacturers who sell "National Match" configuration AR-15 rifles, barrels, and upper receivers. The .223 Wylde achieves better accuracy by having a chamber throat that is tighter than 5.56x45mm but will still function reliably with military 5.56 ammunition as the case dimensions are the same. In short, it will give you the accuracy of a real SAAMI when using the good ammo, but also allow you to use cheap surplus ball ammo safely. Please Google .223 Wylde if you are unfamiliar with this chamber. It is truly the best of both .223 and 5.56 chambers.

postcontent:
This is a Ruger 10/22 hardwood stock that has been modified and reworked. It has a front bedding pillar installed with epoxy action bedding at the take down screw area, and the barrel channel has been relieved so as to free float a factory contour barrel. It has an elegantly tapered forend, asymmetrical modified grip area (suitable for right handed folks), and has been refinished. The wood tint is espresso (that's not the name of the color; I brewed espresso and used it to stain the wood. In fact, I personally roasted raw coffee beans extra dark to get better color), and the finish is poly. It is the same length as a factory carbine stock, and has a standard OEM buttplate.

This stock creates a unique and classic looking 10/22 rifle, and is especially nice with longer sporter barrels. Buy this stock, tell your friends that you made it yourself, and receive a lot of compliments. I won't tell.

Item for sale is stock only, gun not included!

PLEASE NOTE: If you buy this stock and do not have experience tuning 10/22 rifles, please let me help you. Some basic shimming and bedding tips will help your rifle look and shoot better with this stock. I am not an expert, but I can share what I have learned.

All reasonable offers will be considered. Thanks for looking! 

My disclaimer: I stand by my word. I describe item condition honestly, I properly own all items I sell, I only make legal deals with qualified individuals, and I keep appointments. If you are a flake, don’t waste my time. If you don’t keep your word, the deal is null and void. Unless I specifically say I will reserve an item, it is open to the first paying individual. If you say you will buy it and then don’t get around to sending payment quickly, don’t be surprised if someone buys the item out from under you. When you pay, I ship ASAP. If you are unhappy with an item bought from me, I will probably refund your money, less my shipping costs, when you return the item to me promptly and in same condition. title: For Sale:  Unfired PWS MK114 MOD 0 with Upgrades
postcontent:
I'm cleaning out my gun safe as I'm learning a new-born is a bit more important than having guns just sitting in a safe. I picked up this rifle just before I found my son was coming and just never got around to shooting it. For sale is an unfired Primary Weapons Systems (PWS) MK114 MOD 0 with upgraded trigger and buffer tube. If you're looking at this rifle, you know exactly what you're getting. PWS uses a proprietary piston technology which in my opinion is much better than a direct impingement system. This an original MOD 0 rifle which means there are rails all around the upper as opposed to a MOD 1 version which uses the KeyMod rail system. Again, my opinion on the two styles is that the MOD 0 may be a little heavier but you can put just about any attachment on the rails without having to purchase additional rails. Currently, the MOD 1 versions of this rifle cost $1,949 retail (with no upgrades) and take up to 6 months to build/ship. I'm open to REASONABLE offers but new, this rifle would cost you $2,200+.
